.TH "pseries_eeh_init_edev_recursive" 9 "pseries_eeh_init_edev_recursive" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pseries_eeh_init_edev_recursive \- Enable EEH for the indicated device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pseries_eeh_init_edev_recursive
.BI "(struct pci_dn *pdn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdn" 12
PCI device node
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine must be used to perform EEH initialization for the
indicated PCI device that was added after system boot (e.g.
hotplug, dlpar).
